  "chapter": {
    "number": 24,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Job: Judgment for the Wicked"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“Why does the Almighty not reserve times for judgment?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Why may those who know Him never see His days?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Men move boundary stones;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they pasture stolen flocks.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They drive away the donkey of the fatherless",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and take the widow’s ox in pledge.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They push the needy off the road",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and force all the poor of the land into hiding.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Indeed, like wild donkeys in the desert,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the poor go to work foraging for food;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "the wasteland is food for their children.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They gather fodder in the fields",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and glean the vineyards of the wicked.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Without clothing, they spend the night naked;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they have no covering against the cold.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Drenched by mountain rains,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they huddle against the rocks for want of shelter.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The fatherless infant is snatched from the breast;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the nursing child of the poor is seized for a debt.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Without clothing, they wander about naked.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "They carry the sheaves, but still go hungry.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They crush olives within their walls;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they tread the winepresses, but go thirsty.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "From the city, men groan,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the souls of the wounded cry out,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "yet God charges no one with wrongdoing.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Then there are those who rebel against the light,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "not knowing its ways or staying on its paths.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "When daylight is gone, the murderer rises",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to kill the poor and needy;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "in the night he is like a thief.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The eye of the adulterer watches for twilight.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Thinking, ‘No eye will see me,’ he covers his face.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "In the dark they dig through houses;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "by day they shut themselves in,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "never to experience the light.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For to them, deep darkness is their morning;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "surely they are friends with the terrors of darkness!",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They are but foam on the surface of the water;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "their portion of the land is cursed,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "so that no one turns toward their vineyards.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "As drought and heat consume the melting snow,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so Sheol steals those who have sinned.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The womb forgets them;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the worm feeds on them;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "they are remembered no more.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "So injustice is like a broken tree.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They prey on the barren and childless,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and show no kindness to the widow.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Yet by His power, God drags away the mighty;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "though rising up, they have no assurance of life.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He gives them a sense of security,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but His eyes are on their ways.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 24,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They are exalted for a moment,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "then they are gone;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "they are brought low and gathered up like all others;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they are cut off like heads of grain.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 25,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "If this is not so, then who can prove me a liar",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and reduce my words to nothing?”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": []
  },
